label: ACCOUNT
description: Account records store basic account information about your members

label: FMHISTORY
description: This FM History record stores updates to other records in the system when file maintenance occurs.

label: NAME
description: Name records store information about each person who has access to a member's account or to a child record family within the account.

label: LOOKUP
description: You can use Lookup records to cross-reference any identifying number to the Account record.

label: COMMENT
description: Comment records store comment text about the member's account.

label: HOUSEHOLD
description: Household records link accounts belonging to family members living at the same address to the head-of-household account.

label: PREFERENCE
description: The Preference record contains information about a member's preferences for interacting with the audio response or home banking system.

label: PREFERENCE ACCESS
description: These fields store information about Card and Preference Access records.

label: TRACKING
description: Use Tracking records to store any miscellaneous information about the account or to store information about a child record family within the account. Some Tracking records are entered by the system and some are entered by the user.

label: SHARE

description: All Hold records contain the same fields, but Share Hold, Loan Hold, and Portfolio Hold records serve different functions.

label: SHARE TRANSFER
